Radar Base  first appeared as a census designated place in the [[2000 U.S. census]].<ref name=2000CensusTX/>

The population increased in the 2010 census due to the opening of the Maverick County Detention Center; and then decreased prior to the 2020 Census due to the facility's closure in 2015.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Chuy |last= Sanchez|authorlink=   |title= Over 76 Maverick Countians Set to be Laid Off at Maverick County Detention Center  |newspaper=[[Eagle Pass Business Journal]]|date= July 29, 2015|url=https://www.epbusinessjournal.com/2015/07/over-76-maverick-countians-set-to-be-laid-off-at-maverick-county-detention-center/ |via=|archive-url=| archive-date=}}</ref> The facility was purchased by the [[GEO Group]] in 2017 and reopened after the 2020 Census.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Miguel |last=Munoz |authorlink=   |title= The GEO Group, Inc. Acquires Maverick County Detention Center, May Reopen as ICE Detention Center in Near Future  |newspaper=[[Eagle Pass Business Journal]]|date=April 19, 2017 |url= https://www.epbusinessjournal.com/2017/04/the-geo-group-inc-acquires-maverick-county-detention-center-may-reopen-as-ice-detention-center-in-near-future/|via=|archive-url=| archive-date=}}</ref>

